From 164d0738248ac0befb4ce11ca60a06a41838af47 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>
Date: Tue, 10 Dec 2019 07:34:00 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] ALSA: ad1889: Support PCM sync_stop
Git-commit: 164d0738248ac0befb4ce11ca60a06a41838af47
Patch-mainline: v5.6-rc1
References: jsc#SLE-16518

The driver invokes snd_pcm_period_elapsed() simply from the interrupt
handler.  Set card->sync_irq for enabling the missing sync_stop PCM
operation.

Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20191210063454.31603-2-tiwai@suse.de
Signed-off-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 sound/pci/ad1889.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/sound/pci/ad1889.c b/sound/pci/ad1889.c
index 4b902c163fd3..7770157a3a8c 100644
--- a/sound/pci/ad1889.c
+++ b/sound/pci/ad1889.c
@@ -899,7 +899,7 @@ snd_ad1889_create(struct snd_card *card,
 	}
 
 	chip->irq = pci->irq;
-	synchronize_irq(chip->irq);
+	card->sync_irq = chip->irq;
 
 	/* (2) initialization of the chip hardware */
 	if ((err = snd_ad1889_init(chip)) < 0) {
